3.3.2 update 
 
   
void update(float *coord)
    
Convert the given Cartesian x, y, z coordinates in coord to internal
coordinates in-place.  On input, coord[0] should contain the x
coordinate, coord[1] the y coordinate and coord[2] the z coordinate of
an atom position or location.  Upon return coord[0] contains the
distance to the location, coord[1] contains the angle to the two
previous locations and coord[2] the signed torsion to the previous
three locations.

  

  
          
     
        
